'''建議強度評比系統'''（The Grading of Recommendations Assessment, Development and Evaluation approach，簡稱GRADE）是评估[[证据|证据]]的[[确定性|确定性]]和保健建议的一种方法<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Letters, numbers, symbols, and words: How best to communicate grades of evidence and recommendations?|last=[[Holger_Jens_Schünemann|Schünemann]]|first=HJ|last2=Best|first2=D|journal=Canadian Medical Association Journal|issue=7|year=2003|volume=169|pages=677–80|last3=Vist|first3=G|last4=Oxman|first4=AD}}</ref>。GRADE始于2000年。GRADE将证据质量分为高、中、低、极低四个等级。超过100个组织（包括[[世界卫生组织|世界卫生组织]]、哥伦比亚卫生部等）认可和使用GRADE来评估证据的质量和保健建议<ref>{{Cite web|title=GRADEpro|url=https://gradepro.org/resources/#guidelines|accessdate=16 August 2019|work=Gradepro.org|archive-date=2020-09-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200926161646/https://gradepro.org/resources/#guidelines|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=The Saudi Center for Evidence Based Healthcare (EBHC) - Clinical Practice Guidelines|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160225142414/http://www.moh.gov.sa/endepts/Proofs/Pages/Guidelines.aspx|accessdate=2021-02-19|date=2016-02-25|work=web.archive.org}} </ref>。

